  <title>Exercises</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>We haven't actually learned how to do input yet. Some of the exercises in this section have starter code that will allow you to provide input to the program to initialize variables with. Don't worry too much about the syntax for now, just recognize that something like <c>cin >> x;</c> will read a value into x. In this book, the value is read from the textbox below the program.</p>
  </introduction>

